event.title: Thursday Tunes with Shenpa
event.description:
Shenpa is a collective of musicians that makes experimental music that draws inspiration from jazz, funk, hip-hop, world music with a Hindustani classical sentiment. It is a quartet consisting of Jay (guitar, bass, keys, percussion and vocals), Chakshu (percussion), Yuvaan (percussion) and Niranjan (guitar, keys, bass, vocals and percussion). 


The attempt is to find something authentic at the core of the madness that is life by letting go of inhibition. To find something meaningful and authentic in a world where layers of mirages line up on each other to the extent to which you are unable to see the actual reality in front of your eyes. The attempt is to focus on what’s important. To recalibrate the attention on important values and ethics and thinking habits. It’s conscious music for people wanting to become more conscious.


In a given set by the band, one would see the members hopping around on stage going from instrument to instrument saying, singing and rapping things that spike your attention and coaxes you to have new thoughts that are likely to put a smile on your face and have hope for the future. Songs interweave with textures and layers taking the listeners onto a journey of this pursuit. The band makes meaningful use of electronics, synthesis meshes with acoustic organic sounds from the acoustic guitar all the way to glasses and sometimes random material they pick up on the day of the show at the venue.


The sounds are inspired by the environment they find themselves in. Juicy improvisation makes sure each gig unique to itself and resonant with the particular mood of a particular place and the people that happen to be there in that moment. 


It’s a real, organic happening. What you see is what you get. And there is no façade or sense of hiding in the unapologetically honest performance that this band strives to deliver.
